<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf03ba4ef-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8507"><num value="8507">§ 8507.</num><heading> Miscellaneous matters</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf03ba4f0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8507/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Availability of appropriated funds</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Amounts appropriated under this chapter shall remain available until expended.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf03ba4f1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8507/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Of the amounts appropriated to carry out this chapter for a fiscal year, the Secretaries may expend not more than five percent to cover the administrative expenses necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf03ba4f2-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/384/s8">Pub. L. 108–384, § 8</ref>, <date date="2004-10-30">Oct. 30, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/2226">118 Stat. 2226</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
